cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on developing a multi-modal localization system for autonomous vehicles in outdoor environments. Computer Vision (cs.CV) is also a likely sub-category as the system uses vision and LiDAR data for localization. Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) are also possible sub-categories as the system uses semantic data and key-point based visual localization approach. Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) is less likely as there is no mention of language processing in the abstract.
